OL,3,C'Concerning increase' in dog attacks
OL,4,Con postal workers
OL,6,FMost dog attacks took place at the
OL,7,Ffront door, followed by the garden,
OL,8,Fdrive or yard. Some attacks happened
OL,9,Fin the street or road.
OL,11,FOne in five incidents happened through
OL,12,Fletterboxes even though dog owners (or
OL,13,Fthose in care of a dog) can be
OL,14,Fprosecuted if their pets have free
OL,15,Faccess to the letterbox and cause
OL,16,Finjury to any delivery worker whether
OL,17,Fthe owner is at home or not.
