OL,3,C'Concerning increase' in dog attacks
OL,4,Con postal workers
OL,6,FDog attacks resulted in more than
OL,7,F2,273 days of absence in 2023/24, with
OL,8,Fthe longest period of absence being
OL,9,F197 days.
OL,11,FLizz Lloyd, Royal Mail's health &
OL,12,Fsafety director, said: "We are
OL,13,Fsaddened and disappointed to see
OL,14,Fattacks on our staff continue to
OL,15,Fincrease.
OL,17,F"Dog attacks have a devastating effect
OL,18,Fon our people, and we are appealing to
OL,19,Fdog owners to think twice when the
OL,20,Fpostman calls.
